              "keyParts": [
                101,
                "p5",
                "verse",
                "v17",
                "note",
                "f"
              ],
              "value": "tn Following the Hiphil imperative, “bring out,” the three perfect verb forms with vav (ו) consecutive carry an imperatival nuance. For a discussion of the Hebrew construction here and the difficulty of translating it into English, see S. R. Driver, A Treatise on the Use of the Tenses in Hebrew, 124-25."
